{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For multi-task learning, the experiment was repeated with the maximum number of folds of the datasets used, but at least three times.",
    "All models were trained for 20 epochs.",
    "The test set performance within a fold and restart, respectively, was calculated for the epoch with the best validation performance.We compare our results only with approaches that do not exploit the preceding sentence's ground truth labels as a feature during prediction (see Sect. 2.1).",
    "This has a significant impact on the performance: Using the ground truth label of the previous sentences as a sole input feature to an SVM classifier already yields an accuracy of 77.7 for DRI and 55.5 for ART (compare also results for the \"history\" feature in [5]).",
    "Best reported results using ground truth labels as input features have an accuracy of 84.15 for DRI and 65.75 for ART [3]."
  ],
